1
00:00:11,265 --> 00:00:15,210
KOBAYASHI KAORU

2
00:00:16,848 --> 00:00:20,937
TANIMURA MITSUKI
ARATANI KIYOMI

3
00:00:22,597 --> 00:00:25,112
UNO SHOHEI

4
00:00:25,112 --> 00:00:34,692
Kimi ga haita shiroi iki ga ima yukkuri kaze ni notte
<i>Misty white breaths you exhale, now gently riding on the wind</i>

5
00:00:35,212 --> 00:00:45,477
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

6
00:00:45,477 --> 00:00:55,517
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

7
00:00:55,517 --> 00:00:59,610
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

8
00:00:59,610 --> 00:01:04,740
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

9
00:01:04,740 --> 00:01:06,514
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

10
00:01:06,514 --> 00:01:07,120
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

11
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:14,820
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

12
00:01:16,515 --> 00:01:26,460
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

13
00:01:30,492 --> 00:01:36,212
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>

14
00:01:36,212 --> 00:01:40,032
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

15
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:42,702
[Pork Miso Soup Set ¥600, Beer ¥600, Sake ¥500, Shochu ¥400,
Alcoholic drinks are limited to 3 servings]

16
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:45,112
<i>These are the only items on the menu.</i>
[Pork Miso Soup Set ¥600, Beer ¥600, Sake ¥500, Shochu ¥400,
Alcoholic drinks are limited to 3 servings]

17
00:01:45,112 --> 00:01:48,005
<i>If one orders something
aside from these...</i>

18
00:01:48,005 --> 00:01:49,959
<i>...I'll make it if I can.</i>

19
00:01:50,334 --> 00:01:52,864
<i>Such is my business philosophy.</i>

20
00:01:56,912 --> 00:02:01,682
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

21
00:02:03,505 --> 00:02:12,030
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3
EP 4: "Red Pickled Ginger Tempura..."

22
00:02:12,822 --> 00:02:14,852
- Is it okay?
- Slowly, slowly...

23
00:02:14,852 --> 00:02:17,222
- Okay, okay.
- I said slow down!

24
00:02:17,222 --> 00:02:19,562
- Go! Okay, okay...
- Is it okay?

25
00:02:19,562 --> 00:02:21,882
- Yeah, it's fine.
- Thanks!

26
00:02:31,578 --> 00:02:34,878
- See ya.
- Thanks for the help!

27
00:02:35,688 --> 00:02:38,708
Why does he always passes through here?

28
00:02:41,808 --> 00:02:46,128
Delicious! I guess it's still summer, huh?

29
00:02:46,128 --> 00:02:48,538
Such a nice sound...

30
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:52,258
It'll be the festival around here soon, right?

31
00:02:52,258 --> 00:02:55,578
We'll come and wear yukata* here, Master!
(*light kimono)

32
00:02:57,058 --> 00:02:58,748
Oh, you're not happy about that?

33
00:02:59,988 --> 00:03:02,648
It's just that smoke got in my eyes.

34
00:03:04,648 --> 00:03:07,288
Komichi-kun, you don't look so well today, huh.

35
00:03:07,288 --> 00:03:09,318
Well you always look like that though...

36
00:03:09,318 --> 00:03:10,408
He's suffering, y'know.

37
00:03:10,408 --> 00:03:12,438
Eh? Cirrhosis of the liver?

38
00:03:12,438 --> 00:03:15,928
Could it be that you have the same thing
that we suffer from?

39
00:03:15,928 --> 00:03:19,728
Are you in love? With whom?
What kind of person? Is she older? Younger?

40
00:03:19,868 --> 00:03:22,168
Is she a full-time employee?
Or non-regular?

41
00:03:22,168 --> 00:03:24,688
Aren't you guys treating this
like one of your vulgar marriage huntings?

42
00:03:24,688 --> 00:03:28,708
This guy is similar but different.

43
00:03:28,963 --> 00:03:31,443
Well, excuse us.

44
00:03:32,356 --> 00:03:38,128
<i>Originally, Komichi had asked me
for help at the start.</i>

45
00:03:38,128 --> 00:03:40,918
What do you mean by "similar but different".

46
00:03:45,894 --> 00:03:48,712
I'm sorry, Master for always asking for a favor...

47
00:03:49,378 --> 00:03:52,648
I used to make these when I worked part-time
in a street stall a long time ago.

48
00:03:53,442 --> 00:03:55,718
I also bought these. Please use it.

49
00:03:55,718 --> 00:03:57,841
It's okay. 'Cause I have mine.

50
00:03:57,841 --> 00:04:00,141
Oh, of course.

51
00:04:02,078 --> 00:04:05,128
What do you think, Kasumi-san?
Master can cook kushi-age (deep fried skewers), right?

52
00:04:05,128 --> 00:04:08,378
It ain't "kushi-age". It's "kushi-katsu".

53
00:04:08,378 --> 00:04:13,468
<i>Kasumi-chan sometimes shows up
at my shop; she's a Naniwa* girl.</i>
(*former name of Osaka)

54
00:04:13,468 --> 00:04:16,588
<i>This is the girl Kochimi-kun is pining for.</i>

55
00:04:16,588 --> 00:04:20,978
Oh, right. You call it "kushi-katsu" in Osaka, huh?

56
00:04:20,978 --> 00:04:23,298
It's called "kushi-katsu" everywhere.

57
00:04:23,298 --> 00:04:26,318
<i>In order to please the girl he's in love with...</i>

58
00:04:26,318 --> 00:04:30,268
<i>...he orders Osaka specialties for her but...</i>

59
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:35,572
But even though Tokyo kushi-age is all classy,
it tastes all the same.

60
00:04:35,791 --> 00:04:38,236
Well, when compared to the authentic...

61
00:04:39,108 --> 00:04:41,208
I like Master's kushi-age.

62
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:44,148
It's kushi-katsu.

63
00:04:44,148 --> 00:04:46,818
<i>It seems they can't see eye to eye.</i>

64
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:49,938
Oww, oww, hot!

65
00:04:49,938 --> 00:04:52,918
You're kinda clumsy too, eh? Mister.

66
00:04:55,932 --> 00:04:58,728
- This is a bit... Excuse me...
- Oh, okay.
[Pharmacy, 9 am opening]

67
00:05:00,283 --> 00:05:02,468
Okay, here we go...

68
00:05:04,328 --> 00:05:04,856
Yep.

69
00:05:05,574 --> 00:05:08,828
That was nice... Can you
smile a bit more?

70
00:05:08,828 --> 00:05:11,538
- Smile.
- Okay, here we go...

71
00:05:17,798 --> 00:05:20,798
Oh, thanks thanks...

72
00:05:22,558 --> 00:05:24,842
Sorry for asking you to come out so late!

73
00:05:24,842 --> 00:05:26,558
Oh, it's okay. Don't worry about it.

74
00:05:26,558 --> 00:05:29,078
- So where is it?
- This way, sir.

75
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:31,073
Right this way.

76
00:05:31,479 --> 00:05:32,612
Looks nice.

77
00:05:32,792 --> 00:05:35,068
Please, right this way.
It's close.

78
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:36,768
Uh... oh, here?

79
00:05:36,768 --> 00:05:38,668
No, over here.

80
00:05:39,050 --> 00:05:42,753
Ide-san is the president of the pharmacy,
and has branched out into Tokyo...

81
00:05:42,753 --> 00:05:45,049
He has asked me to take pictures
for a publicity magazine.

82
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,578
Well, he asked me for help...

83
00:05:47,578 --> 00:05:50,468
He told me he is at his wit's end
with a girl from Osaka.

84
00:05:50,714 --> 00:05:52,448
I too will give her a good talk...

85
00:05:52,448 --> 00:05:54,968
After that you and her will get along well,
it'll be a breeze!

86
00:05:54,968 --> 00:05:58,208
Thank you. President, would you
like some beer?

87
00:05:58,208 --> 00:06:00,188
Will you be paying?

88
00:06:00,188 --> 00:06:03,308
- Of course.
- Well, good. Don't mind if I do.

89
00:06:03,308 --> 00:06:05,201
Okay. Master, beer.

90
00:06:05,201 --> 00:06:07,781
- Two glasses.
- Sure thing.

91
00:06:08,599 --> 00:06:09,968
- President.
- Huh?

92
00:06:13,868 --> 00:06:15,908
People from Osaka really do that, huh?

93
00:06:15,908 --> 00:06:17,631
What the heck are ya doin...

94
00:06:17,631 --> 00:06:18,791
Bang!

95
00:06:20,378 --> 00:06:21,678
That ain't right.

96
00:06:21,678 --> 00:06:24,198
Your timing is totally wrong.

97
00:06:24,198 --> 00:06:25,768
It's difficult.

98
00:06:25,768 --> 00:06:30,138
We use sophisticated technology when
physical performance is called into question.

99
00:06:30,138 --> 00:06:32,538
There may be the Tokyo Olympics
scoring competition.

100
00:06:32,538 --> 00:06:34,828
If so, I'll be scheduled to be
the Jury President.

101
00:06:34,828 --> 00:06:39,148
Will you be getting tickets for the new
National Stadium? It's still 6 years from now though...

102
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:43,288
It'll be a cinch. No problem.
Do you want to see the 100 meter dash?

103
00:06:43,288 --> 00:06:46,048
No... the women's high jump,
if you please.

104
00:06:46,048 --> 00:06:48,278
That's a good one.

105
00:06:48,948 --> 00:06:50,618
Thanks for waiting.

106
00:06:53,610 --> 00:06:55,000
Welcome.

107
00:06:56,098 --> 00:06:59,488
- Kasumi-san.
- I came just as promised.

108
00:06:59,658 --> 00:07:01,518
What are we gonna eat today?

109
00:07:01,518 --> 00:07:04,818
- Oh, is this the girl?
- Yes.

110
00:07:04,818 --> 00:07:07,068
Where in Osaka are you from?

111
00:07:07,068 --> 00:07:09,408
What? Is this guy your sponsor?

112
00:07:09,553 --> 00:07:11,358
You can trust me.

113
00:07:11,358 --> 00:07:15,848
But before that, Komichi-kun has only
been treating you...

114
00:07:15,848 --> 00:07:18,988
...but you haven't even given him
your cell phone nor email address.

115
00:07:18,988 --> 00:07:21,038
Aintcha being too cruel?

116
00:07:21,038 --> 00:07:24,878
Society is interdependent.
It's a give and take.

117
00:07:24,878 --> 00:07:27,478
Beer and this... make tempura out of it.

118
00:07:32,388 --> 00:07:33,858
Am I gonna fry it as is?

119
00:07:33,858 --> 00:07:37,318
Oh, slice em diagonally...
then plop em in the oil.

120
00:07:42,198 --> 00:07:44,228
She's quite a formidable gal but...

121
00:07:44,228 --> 00:07:46,268
...I find it challenging.

122
00:07:46,268 --> 00:07:48,268
Okay.

123
00:07:54,877 --> 00:07:57,537
How cool is that...

124
00:08:12,938 --> 00:08:14,938
Thanks for waiting.

125
00:08:16,178 --> 00:08:17,818
What is that?

126
00:08:17,818 --> 00:08:19,928
Beniten*.
(*Benishoga or Red pickled ginger Tempura)

127
00:08:19,928 --> 00:08:21,968
Beniten?

128
00:08:26,488 --> 00:08:29,458
Then you began to stock up with benishoga?

129
00:08:29,458 --> 00:08:33,048
Yeah. I buy even those pesky items
that I don't have here.

130
00:08:33,328 --> 00:08:36,198
That Naniwa Girl. What is she?

131
00:08:36,298 --> 00:08:40,368
I asked Komichi-kun what she does but
he said, he doesn't know.

132
00:08:40,662 --> 00:08:43,123
She always doesn't pay for her bills here, right?

133
00:08:43,268 --> 00:08:45,488
Isn't that a nice way of saying,
she's a dine-and-dash girl?

134
00:08:45,646 --> 00:08:47,528
Right~?

135
00:08:47,528 --> 00:08:50,298
- Thanks for waiting.
- Benishoga Tempura...

136
00:08:50,298 --> 00:08:51,658
Would you like some?

137
00:08:52,598 --> 00:08:54,488
No thanks.

138
00:08:55,912 --> 00:08:59,288
Benishoga is good if it
goes with yakisoba but...

139
00:08:59,678 --> 00:09:03,138
The red food coloring looks odious, doesn't it?

140
00:09:03,348 --> 00:09:07,558
I wonder what ingredients they put into it?

141
00:09:07,828 --> 00:09:14,048
I heard they put that in soups in
stand-and-eat soba shops in Akihabara and Asakusa.

142
00:09:14,048 --> 00:09:17,388
- Mm! I can see why...
- Yes! Yes!

143
00:09:17,558 --> 00:09:19,808
It does work!

144
00:09:19,808 --> 00:09:22,398
Indeed...

145
00:09:22,578 --> 00:09:24,828
...it has no shadow (boring and featureless).

146
00:09:24,828 --> 00:09:28,170
In Osaka, they normally sell these as side dishes...

147
00:09:28,357 --> 00:09:30,098
It seems they often eat it at home.

148
00:09:30,357 --> 00:09:34,158
That's impossible. I wonder
if they're born poor over there.

149
00:09:34,158 --> 00:09:36,968
Wait, you don't have to say it that far!
(Note: he suddenly speaks in Osaka dialect)

150
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:43,098
Kou-chan... you're...

151
00:09:43,098 --> 00:09:46,898
I have come here to eat dinner.

152
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:19,109
♫ Kon'na yoru daremoga warai uka re teru kisetsu
<i>Such seasonal evening with everyone laughing merrily</i>

153
00:10:19,109 --> 00:10:29,699
♫ Sake o nomi, uta o utai, shinda yo ni yoruru no sa
<i>Drinking and singing songs, until the night dies</i>

154
00:10:30,224 --> 00:10:35,665
♫ Doko made mo, doko made mo
<i>Wherever, wherever</i>

155
00:10:35,665 --> 00:10:39,820
♫ Tabi wa hatenaku tsudzuku ka
<i>Will the journey end or continue</i>

156
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:44,820
♫ Deau saki de warai ai
<i>To laugh and get along with people you'll meet ahead</i>

157
00:10:45,257 --> 00:10:46,694
♫ Wakareru toki ne
<i>In another time</i>

158
00:10:46,694 --> 00:10:49,284
Chief! Beniten for me too.

159
00:10:49,501 --> 00:10:51,781
Sorry but I'm all out.

160
00:10:52,079 --> 00:10:56,411
I have some other minced stuff though.
I could fry that up for you if you like.

161
00:10:56,411 --> 00:10:59,011
I don't want that. Missy...

162
00:10:59,011 --> 00:11:01,081
Can you share one with me?

163
00:11:01,081 --> 00:11:03,411
- These are mine.
- How much did you pay for it?

164
00:11:03,813 --> 00:11:05,361
One million yen.
(In Osaka shops, they would jokingly refer to 1 yen
as 1 million yen, 5 yen = 5 million yen and so forth)

165
00:11:05,361 --> 00:11:07,551
How cheap, huh?
(In Osaka shops, they would jokingly refer to 1 yen
as 1 million yen, 5 yen = 5 million yen and so forth)

166
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:09,741
Well, then. I'm done.

167
00:11:09,741 --> 00:11:13,561
- Komichi-kun, you pick up the tab, okay?
- Huh? But the other day...

168
00:11:13,561 --> 00:11:15,781
That was for the other day.
Now is now.

169
00:11:16,041 --> 00:11:18,141
Circumstances always changes.

170
00:11:18,141 --> 00:11:21,441
You want an Olympic
platinum diamond ticket, doncha?

171
00:11:21,441 --> 00:11:22,571
Oh...

172
00:11:22,921 --> 00:11:26,151
Mister. Your wig is showing.

173
00:11:26,391 --> 00:11:30,471
Don't say stupid things.
This ain't a wig.

174
00:11:30,471 --> 00:11:34,221
She's right. There's no reason to wear
such an obvious wig, right?

175
00:11:34,841 --> 00:11:37,451
Uh... no... um...

176
00:11:38,241 --> 00:11:40,251
I think it's better if you take it off.

177
00:11:49,931 --> 00:11:52,931
She's really an interesting gal...

178
00:11:58,431 --> 00:12:00,841
Here.

179
00:12:01,621 --> 00:12:03,141
Thanks.

180
00:12:11,091 --> 00:12:12,691
- Welcome.
- Hello.

181
00:12:22,811 --> 00:12:25,981
- Can I also have Beniten?
- Good for one person?

182
00:12:25,981 --> 00:12:28,466
No no, I usually order half, right?

183
00:12:28,466 --> 00:12:31,122
Who'd pay 400 yen for such a thing...

184
00:12:31,371 --> 00:12:33,445
I used to pay 5 yen for each piece.

185
00:12:33,445 --> 00:12:35,008
Sure thing.

186
00:12:35,741 --> 00:12:40,431
And also some cold tea.

187
00:12:40,431 --> 00:12:42,761
President, your head...

188
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:45,951
- Oh, you noticed?
- I could see it.

189
00:12:45,951 --> 00:12:48,381
You're a breath of fresh air.

190
00:12:48,651 --> 00:12:53,281
As merchants say, "It's bad,
if you're afraid of change."

191
00:12:55,976 --> 00:13:00,161
Ide-san... Take only 3 toothpicks here.

192
00:13:00,161 --> 00:13:03,171
Come on, don't be so stingy.

193
00:13:03,541 --> 00:13:07,251
The owner here is so stingy.

194
00:13:08,501 --> 00:13:11,071
Well, Missy, whatchu think?

195
00:13:11,234 --> 00:13:13,531
- About what?
- About this.

196
00:13:13,906 --> 00:13:16,231
I wonder if it's more interesting
if you wear a wig?

197
00:13:17,661 --> 00:13:19,391
But it looks cute.

198
00:13:20,523 --> 00:13:21,312
Cute?

199
00:13:21,890 --> 00:13:25,771
It suits you. It's like Billiken-san*,
when he grants your wish...
(*Good luck image of a bald, smiling man)

200
00:13:25,771 --> 00:13:31,401
How about it, Missy? You want to be
my mistress? If you want money, I have plenty.

201
00:13:32,191 --> 00:13:35,011
My mom said...

202
00:13:35,271 --> 00:13:38,381
"Don't become just a cheap mistress."

203
00:13:38,381 --> 00:13:42,011
Well, goodbye. Pay for my tab, okay?

204
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:52,791
She really is one interesting gal...

205
00:13:53,390 --> 00:13:58,241
<i>If you've grown bored of such
Osaka dialect exchange...</i>

206
00:13:58,241 --> 00:14:03,841
<i>...be on your guard.
Disaster strikes when you least expect it.</i>

207
00:14:04,507 --> 00:14:06,390
- Thanks for waiting.
- Thank you.

208
00:14:06,390 --> 00:14:10,390
C'mon, let's just try it out once.
As they say...

209
00:14:10,539 --> 00:14:13,871
..."you can't judge a horse
until you've ridden it", right?

210
00:14:13,871 --> 00:14:16,671
I've already cured my gum disease.

211
00:14:20,081 --> 00:14:22,391
Your nose is like a marshmallow.

212
00:14:22,882 --> 00:14:26,151
- Good evening.
- Welcome!

213
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:28,601
Honey!

214
00:14:28,601 --> 00:14:30,441
When you said you'd be working late...

215
00:14:30,441 --> 00:14:32,541
...I knew you're going out occasionally.

216
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:35,591
I- I wasn't doing anything...

217
00:14:35,591 --> 00:14:37,881
Eh? How come you know I'm here...

218
00:14:37,881 --> 00:14:43,111
I ordered plenty of detectives to
watch you closely.

219
00:14:43,331 --> 00:14:46,041
I've even called former CIA agent, Snowden.

220
00:14:46,041 --> 00:14:50,011
Really? It's globalization, ain't it?

221
00:14:50,395 --> 00:14:51,551
You dumb stupid scum!

222
00:14:51,738 --> 00:14:55,751
How old do you think you are?
You sex-obsessed fiend.

223
00:14:55,751 --> 00:14:59,051
I'll get yours, Mister.

224
00:14:59,238 --> 00:15:00,911
How pathetic!

225
00:15:02,591 --> 00:15:04,341
Let's go home! Goodness...

226
00:15:04,341 --> 00:15:06,949
- Ah! Your change!
- Oh, right.

227
00:15:07,184 --> 00:15:09,571
Here's 5 million yen.

228
00:15:12,191 --> 00:15:14,231
Oh, you're learning well.

229
00:15:14,231 --> 00:15:15,886
That was good.

230
00:15:16,034 --> 00:15:18,691
You're such a loser!

231
00:15:20,121 --> 00:15:23,361
I enjoyed the service.
If you'll excuse me.

232
00:15:24,791 --> 00:15:26,661
<i>Honey~!</i>

233
00:15:35,437 --> 00:15:40,657
<i>It had been a while since that uproar...</i>

234
00:15:51,047 --> 00:15:53,987
It's good that it was found out early.

235
00:15:53,987 --> 00:15:57,107
Just focus on having it cured through surgery.

236
00:15:57,107 --> 00:15:59,397
Don't say such a thing so easily.

237
00:16:00,227 --> 00:16:02,627
If the surgery fails...

238
00:16:04,627 --> 00:16:08,707
If I'll lose my crown jewels...

239
00:16:09,237 --> 00:16:14,037
...there'll be nothing to look
forward to in life anymore.

240
00:16:19,877 --> 00:16:22,437
- Missy.
- What?

241
00:16:22,437 --> 00:16:25,117
I'll have surgery the day after tomorrow.

242
00:16:25,117 --> 00:16:29,357
If so, I will no longer be able to satisfy you.

243
00:16:29,927 --> 00:16:34,007
Please... Can you spend the night with me?

244
00:16:34,007 --> 00:16:37,031
President! You said you're gonna
stop being irresponsible...

245
00:16:37,202 --> 00:16:38,887
Fine.

246
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:43,374
Well, let's go. Pay for my tab.

247
00:16:46,637 --> 00:16:50,637
Um... uh... I'm done. Thanks.

248
00:17:04,087 --> 00:17:09,037
There's a chance that he lied
about having surgery, right? Master.

249
00:17:12,137 --> 00:17:14,347
Hotel's over there.

250
00:17:14,347 --> 00:17:17,657
- You still don't know yet?
- Don't worry.

251
00:17:17,657 --> 00:17:20,807
If it's spending money,
I'll give you plenty to splurge on.

252
00:17:23,257 --> 00:17:25,847
"Don't become just a cheap mistress..."

253
00:17:25,847 --> 00:17:30,487
That's what my mom told me
long before she went to heaven.

254
00:17:30,487 --> 00:17:34,157
Right! Let's both go to heaven too, you and I.

255
00:17:34,157 --> 00:17:35,617
So let's go. Come on.

256
00:17:35,617 --> 00:17:38,177
Look and you'll know right away.

257
00:17:38,177 --> 00:17:40,067
Know what?

258
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:41,827
Beniten...

259
00:17:41,827 --> 00:17:44,527
...is the flavor I associate with my mom
and my fatherless family...

260
00:17:44,527 --> 00:17:47,117
It's the taste of poverty.

261
00:17:47,117 --> 00:17:49,537
Even if it's for being nothing
but getting stabbed in the back...

262
00:17:49,537 --> 00:17:52,177
...it's bad if you don't express your gratitude...

263
00:17:52,177 --> 00:17:54,177
...Dad.

264
00:17:55,457 --> 00:17:57,627
Who are you?

265
00:17:57,627 --> 00:18:01,727
There's no way you'd know, huh.
I was just born during that time.

266
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:05,857
What are you saying?

267
00:18:05,857 --> 00:18:09,937
Take a look at my face.
There's a trace of it, right?

268
00:18:09,937 --> 00:18:13,657
25 years ago, the woman you discarded
in Higashi-Sumiyoshi...

269
00:18:13,657 --> 00:18:15,757
...was my mom.

270
00:18:43,107 --> 00:18:44,627
Thanks.

271
00:18:48,207 --> 00:18:52,167
Oh! This is super-duper good!

272
00:18:53,067 --> 00:18:55,237
Your surgery was a success...

273
00:18:55,237 --> 00:18:57,867
From here on, focus on the business, okay?

274
00:18:57,867 --> 00:19:00,807
I know that. You don't have
to say anything more.

275
00:19:00,807 --> 00:19:03,097
I won't be here if it weren't for you.

276
00:19:03,097 --> 00:19:05,497
You can count on me from here on too.

277
00:19:05,497 --> 00:19:08,247
You really are a devil.

278
00:19:08,247 --> 00:19:10,287
Oh, wait... it shifted too much...

279
00:19:24,227 --> 00:19:29,617
What is this, no message but
only a picture of beniten.

280
00:19:29,617 --> 00:19:31,307
Is this some kind of cryptic message?

281
00:19:31,307 --> 00:19:34,257
Gimme a break, Honey...

282
00:19:34,257 --> 00:19:38,527
I have really drawn the line between
me and that girl. Please believe me.

283
00:19:38,527 --> 00:19:42,417
If you've drawn the line, then you wouldn't
be getting this, would you?

284
00:19:42,997 --> 00:19:44,997
Well...

285
00:19:44,997 --> 00:19:47,607
How much is this phone?

286
00:19:48,237 --> 00:19:51,537
Ah~ 3,000 yen.

287
00:19:51,537 --> 00:19:53,577
Well, then good.

288
00:19:54,947 --> 00:19:56,767
When the asking price is like that in business...

289
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:59,887
...it's disgrace to a merchant's reputation.

290
00:19:59,887 --> 00:20:01,727
Right?

